{
  "slug": "tapestry-cartoon-and-transfer",
  "title": "Tapestry cartoon and transfer",
  "subtitle": "Drawing and transferring a full-scale design to the tapestry loom",
  "excerpt": "The tapestry cartoon is a full-scale drawing placed behind the warp to guide the weaving. Getting the scale right and marking the right amount of detail on the cartoon before you begin saves significant time at the loom.",
  "type": "TECHNIQUE",
  "categorySlug": "fibre-arts",
  "subCategorySlug": "weaving",
  "difficulty": "INTERMEDIATE",
  "season": null,
  "sourceType": "PUBLIC_DOMAIN",
  "sourceNotes": "- Hooper, Luther. Hand-Loom Weaving: Plain and Ornamental. Pitman, 1910. Available via Internet Archive. Describes cartoon preparation and transfer for tapestry weaving.",
  "recipeTools": [
    {
      "slug": "tapestry-loom-upright",
      "isOptional": false
    },
    {
      "slug": "measuring-tape-soft",
      "isOptional": false
    },
    {
      "slug": "craft-scissors",
      "isOptional": false
    }
  ],
  "glossaryTerms": [
    {
      "slug": "cartoon",
      "term": "Cartoon",
      "definition": "A full-scale drawing placed behind or traced onto the warp as a weaving guide."
    },
    {
      "slug": "warp",
      "term": "Warp",
      "definition": "The vertical threads under tension on the loom."
    },
    {
      "slug": "weft",
      "term": "Weft",
      "definition": "The horizontal threads woven across the warp."
    },
    {
      "slug": "sett",
      "term": "Sett",
      "definition": "The number of warp threads per centimetre or inch; determines the fineness of the weave."
    },
    {
      "slug": "pick-count",
      "term": "Pick count",
      "definition": "The number of weft rows (picks) per centimetre or inch in the finished weave."
    }
  ],
  "techniqueSlugs": [],
  "criticalTechniques": [],
  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "cartoon",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "cartoon"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " is the full-scale drawing placed behind the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "warp",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "warp"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " to guide the placement of each colour area. It removes the need to measure or estimate shapes during weaving. The better your "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "cartoon",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "cartoon"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " is prepared, the more freely you can focus on the weaving itself."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "suppliesCard",
        "attrs": {
          "items": [
            "Paper large enough to match the planned weaving dimensions (lining paper or joined sheets work well)",
            "Ruler and pencil",
            "Black marker pen (for the traced outline on the warp)",
            "Tape measure",
            "Photocopier or printer with enlargement capability (optional)",
            "Scissors or craft knife"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Scaling the design"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Measure the weaving area on your loom: the width between the outermost "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "warp",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "warp"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " threads, and the planned height in centimetres. This is the exact size your "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "cartoon",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "cartoon"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " must be."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Step 1: Draw or print your design at a small scale first: a thumbnail sketch showing proportions and major colour areas."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Step 2: Use a grid to scale up: draw a grid over the thumbnail (say, 1 cm squares), then draw a matching grid at full scale on the large paper (each 1 cm square becomes, for example, 5 cm). Copy the design square by square."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Step 3: If the design is a digital image, print it tiled across A4 sheets at the right total size. Tape the sheets together and trim to size."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "How much detail to include"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "cartoon",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "cartoon"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " does not need shading or fine gradations. The weaving process itself will simplify the image: very fine lines and subtle colour transitions tend to disappear at low "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "sett",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "sett"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " values. What the cartoon must have, clearly marked:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "The outer boundary of every colour area, drawn in bold black line."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "A colour notation (number, letter, or colour swatch) inside each area."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Horizontal lines marking key row counts: for example, every 10 rows if your "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "pick count",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                        "attrs": {
                          "termSlug": "pick-count"
                        }
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " is known."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Marking key rows on the cartoon"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Calculate your approximate "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "pick count",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "pick-count"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " (rows per centimetre) from a small test sample. Multiply that number by the height in centimetres to get the total row count. Draw horizontal lines across the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "cartoon",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "cartoon"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " at the actual millimetre positions corresponding to every 10 rows (or 20 rows for a coarser "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "sett",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "sett"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "). Annotate each line with the row number. These markers let you check your weaving rate as you work rather than discovering a size error at the end."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Transferring the cartoon to the loom"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "There are three practical methods for getting the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "cartoon",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "cartoon"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " onto the loom."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Step 1: Hang behind. Attach the cartoon behind the warp with tape or clips so it is visible through the warp threads. This is the simplest method for a frame loom with a sparse warp. Weave from the front, referring to the cartoon through the gaps."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Step 2: Trace onto the warp. Lay the cartoon flat on a table; place the warped frame on top, aligned. Use a waterproof black marker to trace the colour-area outlines directly onto the warp threads. The marker lines stay visible as the weaving progresses and the "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "weft",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                        "attrs": {
                          "termSlug": "weft"
                        }
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " covers them."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Step 3: Photocopy method. If a photocopier with enlargement is available, enlarge the design to the exact weaving dimensions in sections, piece the sections together on the back of the loom, and weave with the cartoon in place behind the "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "warp",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                        "attrs": {
                          "termSlug": "warp"
                        }
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "What the weaving naturally simplifies"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Tapestry steps in increments of one "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "warp",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "warp"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " thread horizontally and one "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "pick count",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "pick-count"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " row vertically. Diagonals in the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "cartoon",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "cartoon"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " become staircase steps in the weaving. Fine curves turn into blocky approximations. Accept this early rather than fighting it: the staircase character is part of tapestry's aesthetic. Draw the cartoon with bold, clear colour boundaries rather than fine gradations, since gradations simply will not survive the translation."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "items": [
            {
              "problem": "The weaving is growing taller than the cartoon predicted",
              "solution": "Your pick count is lower than you sampled. Check whether you are beating less firmly than in the sample. Add more horizontal row-marker lines to the cartoon going forward and adjust your beating pressure."
            },
            {
              "problem": "The cartoon trace lines are disappearing under the weft before the colour area is finished",
              "solution": "Use a thicker marker pen for tracing, or re-mark the lines with a fresh pass before weaving the next section. Waterproof permanent marker holds better than water-based felt-tip."
            },
            {
              "problem": "The design looks correct on the cartoon but the weaving drifts off-centre",
              "solution": "The cartoon was not aligned square to the warp before tracing. Check that the bottom edge of the cartoon is parallel to the bottom selvedge rod, and that the sides align with the outermost warp threads, before tracing."
            }
          ]
        }
      }
    ]
  }
}
